<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="913" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d913">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15294.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State ad
                                    interim</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to
                                    Mexico</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-15T15:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1915—3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>777. Please deliver the following message to President Lagos Cházaro, and
                            a copy to Gonzalez Garza.</p>
                        <p>[Quotes message from Villa transmitted in Mr. Carothers’ June 11,
                            noon.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>